like. Accordingly, the book provides a typology of alliances that distinguishes four possible types and sheds light on interallied relations, indicating their causes and effects. Historical case studies from 18th-century Europe, beginning with the War of the Spanish Succession and proceeding chronologically until the eve of the French Revolution, offer readers an overview of almost the entire century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aPolitics -- International Relations. 4aPolitics -- Theory and Methods. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362737640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503627376423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503627376/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles